messages.messageBody:
and that isn't just buttering you all up!

Thanks by the way for all the reading info. I do know not to go to fast or
get pushy, made that mistake already, and want to thank you all for your
advice....

but now to the completely and wildly off topic part.

I'm trying to find info out for someone else who is suffering from
infertility due to high FSH level. This person will be 41 this year, and her
FSH level was 15.8. I know next to nothing about this. Anyone who has info
on how to become pregnant with high FSH levels, write me please? But only
infertility/high fsh info...whatever it took. Herbs, allopathic medicine,
egg donations... whatever...I need to give the info to this other person who
is not the internet fiend that I am....

Thanks all....

be well,
Rachel Ann
